{"id":"abishua","term":"Abishua","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>Father of welfare; i.e., “fortunate.” (1.) The grandson of Benjamin (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 8:4\">1 Chr. 8:4</a>).</p>\n<p>(2.) The son of Phinehas the high priest (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 6:4\">1 Chr. 6:4</a>,<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 6:5\">5</a>,<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 6:50\">50</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Ezra 7:5\">Ezra 7:5</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["1 Chronicles 8:4","1 Chronicles 6:4","1 Chronicles 6:5","1 Chronicles 6:50","Ezra 7:5"]}